Summer is upon us in New Zealand. When I create a new recipe,
I love to bring in fresh natural flavours using seasonal produce.
This provides a unique taste experience, texture and nutritional
balance to the dish. There is nothing better than enjoying the
sweet juiciness of a ripe summer tomato. They are terrific roasted,
their flavour is intensified with long slow cooking, served with lemon
caramelised snapper they're superb. New Zealand kelp is a type of
seaweed that once dried, has a lovely tresn salty tavour ana makes
a fantastic seasoning. The menu at Vinnies is my canvas on which
to paint and create dishes using only the tresnest proauce.
I take my ideas and develop them into dishes to enhance your dining
experience on Air New Zealand - I hope you enjoy your meal.
GEOFF SCOTT
OWNER AND CHEF, VINNIES RESTAURANT, HERNE BAY, AUCKLAND
